</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,283,1270]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,435,1084,1110]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Remarks:</emphasis>
This new species is close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Flechtmann, 2002" authorityName="Flechtmann" authorityYear="2002" box="[791,1272,1084,1110]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Abacarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nectandrae">
<emphasis box="[791,1045,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="39">Abacarus nectandrae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Flechtmann, C. - H. - W." box="[1054,1272,1084,1110]" pageId="4" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref4066" refString="Flechtmann, C. - H. - W. (2002) Three new species of eriophyid mites (Acari: Eriophyidae) from Sao Paulo, Brazil. Zootaxa, 23, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2002">Flechtmann, 2002</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs in the shield design with median line present on posterior 1/2, coxae with a sternal line, coxal area smooth and female genital coverflap with 10 longitudinal ridges.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="39" type="etymology">
